{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-market-data-service-collection",
    "name": "AGCE — market-data-service",
    "description": "REST API for the AGCE market-data-service — the unified market-data gateway.\n\nThe REST endpoints in this collection proxy Binance public snapshots (exchangeInfo, depth, trades, klines, tickers) used to bootstrap the trading UI. Live streaming (which is the main feature of this service) is Socket.IO and is not Postman-testable — see the Socket.IO section below.\n\n**Setup**\n1. Import this collection AND the environment (`market-data-service.postman_environment.json`).\n2. Select the `market-data-service (local)` environment in Postman.\n3. Make sure `market-data-service` is running locally (`npm run dev` or `skaffold dev`).\n4. The `baseUrl` is `http://localhost:3002` direct, or `http://localhost:8080` through the gateway (recommended — that's the same origin the frontend uses).\n\n**Authentication**\nPublic market data endpoints currently do not require a token. If you wrap the routes in `requireAuth`, set `accessToken` from auth_service's `/auth/login` response and the Bearer header is applied automatically.\n\n**Socket.IO — live streams (NOT Postman-testable)**\n\nThe frontend opens ONE Socket.IO connection to this service and receives TWO upstream sources:\n\n1. **Binance reference data** — `emit(\"subscribe\", { channel: \"depth\"|\"trade\"|\"kline\"|\"ticker\"|..., symbol })`. Events arrive on `\"data\"`.\n\n2. **AGCE local matching events** — `emit(\"subscribe\", { channel: \"local_trade\"|\"local_depth\", symbol: \"BTC-USDT\" })`. Events arrive on `local:trade:<SYMBOL>` / `local:depth:<SYMBOL>`. Forwarded from matching_service via the `matching.trades` / `matching.depth-updates` Kafka topics.\n\nEvery payload carries a `source: \"binance\" | \"local\"` flag. **Binance rows are display-only — §23 hard constraint.** User orders never match against them; they go to matching_service and match against local liquidity only.\n\nSee `../architecture.md` for the full subscribe protocol, room naming, disconnect handling, and frontend example.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{accessToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Healthz",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/healthz",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["healthz"]
            },
            "description": "Kubernetes liveness probe. Always 200 once the HTTP server is up."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Connectivity",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Ping Binance",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/binance/ping",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "binance", "ping"]
            },
            "description": "Proxies Binance /api/v3/ping. 200 = Binance is reachable."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Server Time",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/binance/time",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "binance", "time"]
            },
            "description": "Returns Binance server time in ms. Useful for clock-skew detection."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Exchange",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Exchange Info — all symbols",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/binance/exchangeInfo",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "binance", "exchangeInfo"]
            },
            "description": "Metadata for ALL Binance spot symbols. Cache for ≥1h on the frontend.\n\nResponse is large (~2MB). Use this once at app boot."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Exchange Info — single symbol",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/binance/exchangeInfo?symbol={{symbol}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "binance", "exchangeInfo"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "symbol",
                  "value": "{{symbol}}",
                  "description": "Trading pair, e.g. BTCUSDT"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Same as above but limited to one symbol. Use to validate order form filters (LOT_SIZE, PRICE_FILTER, MIN_NOTIONAL)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Market Data",
      "item": [
